title: Grateful Dead Live at Field House, Northern Illinois U on 1977-10-29
description:
Set 1

Might As Well, Jack Straw, Dire Wolf, Looks Like Rain, Loser, El Paso, Ramble On Rose, Minglewood Blues, It Must Have Been The Roses, Let It Grow

Set 2

Bertha-> Good Lovin', Friend Of The Devil, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Saint Stephen-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia-> Drums-> Sunshine Daydream, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: What a show! This one is a gem. Too many great moments to mention. This recording is really good, can't believe it hasn't been reviewed. You can tell its gonna be smokin from the might as well opener....Jerry woopin and hollerin at the end. Killer show, crowd is loving it.

The best of the smalls I went to this show, downstate of Chicago. We all were driving down there passing car after car of happy Dead Heads all in costumes, or it was hard to tell. I probably went as a pirate. People talk a lot about this show, hell I didn't even know it was on CD!!! Such a fantastic performance, back when the GD played 4–5-hour shows~
Northern! I went to Northern and am a massive Deadhead.  This is a legendary show.  Get it!
